Yes, there are almost a thousand arches.

269
00:15:07,627 --> 00:15:09,627
A thousand?

270
00:15:09,627 --> 00:15:12,327
Are we going to walk up there?

271
00:15:12,327 --> 00:15:14,327
We have no choice.

272
00:15:18,897 --> 00:15:20,899
I can't do it!

273
00:15:20,899 --> 00:15:23,827
Come on, Genta!

274
00:15:23,827 --> 00:15:26,027
Just a little more!

275
00:15:34,127 --> 00:15:35,427
We made it!

276
00:15:36,227 --> 00:15:39,427
-It's pretty. -Look at the view!

277
00:15:39,427 --> 00:15:44,923
So what does " Below the top of the hidden Inari" mean?

278
00:15:44,923 --> 00:15:46,427
Hey, what's that?

279
00:15:46,427 --> 00:15:50,027
-Is it food? -Fried tofu?

280
00:15:50,027 --> 00:15:52,931
That is not for eating. It's an offering.

281
00:15:53,127 --> 00:15:56,227
Because fried tofu is the fox's favorite food.

282
00:15:56,227 --> 00:15:58,937
Where do they put them?

283
00:15:58,937 --> 00:16:00,627
Are you planning to steal them?

284
00:16:00,627 --> 00:16:02,527
You'll get punished!

285
00:16:02,527 --> 00:16:05,527
I'm just asking!

286
00:16:05,527 --> 00:16:08,427
They either put it at the main building,

287
00:16:08,427 --> 00:16:11,327
or in the shrine at the back.

288
00:16:11,327 --> 00:16:15,227
Maybe that's the hidden Inari?

289
00:16:19,327 --> 00:16:20,959
Here?

290
00:16:21,127 --> 00:16:23,927
I don't see anything.

291
00:16:23,927 --> 00:16:26,327
I found the fried tofu!

292
00:16:26,327 --> 00:16:28,967
Now you know you can't get them.

293
00:16:28,967 --> 00:16:32,327
-I said I'm not! -This is awesome.

294
00:16:32,327 --> 00:16:34,527
Hey guys, look at this!

295
00:16:34,527 --> 00:16:37,627
So many foxes in there!

296
00:16:37,627 --> 00:16:38,977
You're right.

297
00:16:38,977 --> 00:16:40,979
It's cool.

298
00:16:40,979 --> 00:16:44,983
I know! The hidden Inari is around here!

299
00:16:44,983 --> 00:16:47,727
No, not there, it's here.

300
00:16:50,989 --> 00:16:54,327
This is the hidden Inari.

301
00:16:54,327 --> 00:16:57,527
Now, "Below the top of the hidden Inari"

302
00:16:57,527 --> 00:17:00,999
There is a fried tofu figure made of stone.

303
00:17:00,999 --> 00:17:02,627
Fried tofu?

304
00:17:02,627 --> 00:17:05,327
I got it! The kanji that means "Top"

305
00:17:05,327 --> 00:17:07,005
also could translate to the meaning of fried tofu.

306
00:17:07,227 --> 00:17:11,527
So the treasure should be under the fried tofu made of stone!

307
00:17:11,527 --> 00:17:15,627
-Awesome, Mitsuhiko! -You are a genius!

308
00:17:15,627 --> 00:17:17,727
Thanks, guys!

309
00:17:19,927 --> 00:17:21,019
A jar?

310
00:17:22,027 --> 00:17:23,927
What's in there?

311
00:17:23,927 --> 00:17:27,927
Well, there is some kind of paper.

312
00:17:27,927 --> 00:17:29,927
This is...

313
00:17:29,927 --> 00:17:31,627
It looks like a map.

314
00:17:31,627 --> 00:17:34,027
There's something written on the top!

315
00:17:34,027 --> 00:17:35,727
What does it say?

316
00:17:35,727 --> 00:17:37,727
"Reflect the castle in the eye of the cat"

317
00:17:37,727 --> 00:17:40,227
"and look under the mouse."

318
00:17:40,227 --> 00:17:41,827
What does that mean?

319
00:17:41,827 --> 00:17:43,727
A cat...

320
00:17:44,327 --> 00:17:47,045
It should be about this.

321
00:17:47,045 --> 00:17:49,527
I see holes in it.

322
00:17:49,527 --> 00:17:53,051
Not a mouse in any of the pages.

323
00:17:53,051 --> 00:17:55,327
Another puzzle, huh?

324
00:17:55,327 --> 00:18:00,427
This seems like the old map of the city of Hagi.

325
00:18:00,427 --> 00:18:03,427
Hagi is in Yamaguchi Prefecture.

326
00:18:03,427 --> 00:18:08,327
Yes, the city is linked to Shouin whom my grandfather adored.

327
00:18:08,327 --> 00:18:12,627
I see, so the treasure should be in Hagi.

328
00:18:13,427 --> 00:18:16,727
I see. They are headed for Hagi.

329
00:18:16,727 --> 00:18:20,127
Stay with them, you hear me?

330
00:18:24,527 --> 00:18:26,727
Where is Kimiko?

331
00:18:27,827 --> 00:18:30,227
I'm coming!

332
00:18:39,527 --> 00:18:41,927
It feels like a very old town.

333
00:18:41,927 --> 00:18:45,427
They have preserved the town as it is was like in the old days.

334
00:18:45,427 --> 00:18:48,227
So you can even walk through the town

335
00:18:48,227 --> 00:18:50,727
even if you had a map from the Edo Period!

336
00:18:50,727 --> 00:18:52,327
That is marvelous!

337
00:18:52,327 --> 00:18:55,113
The many people who were involved in the Meiji Restoration

338
00:18:55,113 --> 00:18:57,115
have also seen this same view today.

339
00:18:57,115 --> 00:19:00,527
That's right! This is where the Meiji Restoration all began!

340
00:19:00,527 --> 00:19:02,927
Here we go. The Meiji Reservation.

341
00:19:02,927 --> 00:19:05,127
Restoration!

342
00:19:05,127 --> 00:19:07,927
That's the reform that gave Japan its chance

343
00:19:07,927 --> 00:19:10,227
to become a modern country like it is today.

344
00:19:10,227 --> 00:19:13,127
Many people who were involved in the Meiji Restoration

345
00:19:13,127 --> 00:19:15,127
were from Hagi.

346
00:19:15,127 --> 00:19:16,527
I see!

347
00:19:16,527 --> 00:19:19,137
"Hagi Museum East Entrance"

348
00:19:20,827 --> 00:19:22,627
The Cat Street?

349
00:19:23,327 --> 00:19:25,427
Does this have anything to do with that code?

350
00:19:25,427 --> 00:19:31,149
About 250 streets are named like that.

351
00:19:31,149 --> 00:19:34,527
This street is named after a person who was close to Terumoto Mouri,

352
00:19:34,527 --> 00:19:37,627
and since he was fond of cats,

353
00:19:37,627 --> 00:19:39,927
they called it the Cat Street.

354
00:19:41,159 --> 00:19:43,161
Look! A real cat!

355
00:19:43,161 --> 00:19:47,827
Oh, kitty cat! I know, I got it!

356
00:19:47,827 --> 00:19:50,227
You mean you solved the puzzle?

357
00:19:50,227 --> 00:19:51,169
Yes!

358
00:19:51,327 --> 00:19:54,627
They meant the white walls, not the castle!

359
00:19:54,627 --> 00:19:57,827
That means that one of these cats is watching a wall

360
00:19:57,827 --> 00:20:01,827
which will point out where the treasure is!

361
00:20:01,827 --> 00:20:05,183
And that cat right there is looking at it right...

362
00:20:05,183 --> 00:20:07,185
Wait! Please wait, Kitty!

363
00:20:07,185 --> 00:20:10,227
I'm very sure that he is wrong.

364
00:20:10,227 --> 00:20:13,527
Mr. Mouri sure has a sense of humor.

365
00:20:13,527 --> 00:20:16,227
The problem is that he's dead serious.

366
00:20:21,199 --> 00:20:24,427
That was the guy who called himself Shigeru Kawaguchi?

367
00:20:29,207 --> 00:20:31,527
Can't you understand what I'm saying?

368
00:20:31,527 --> 00:20:33,527
But...

369
00:20:33,527 --> 00:20:35,827
It is him.

370
00:20:37,215 --> 00:20:38,327
That man...

371
00:20:40,727 --> 00:20:43,221
The guy who attacked Kimiko!

372
00:20:44,727 --> 00:20:48,127
This is where the doctor in the Edo period named Shusuke Aoki

373
00:20:48,127 --> 00:20:49,727
was living.

374
00:20:49,727 --> 00:20:52,427
They say that they found treasure buried here.

375
00:20:52,427 --> 00:20:54,327
You know well!

376
00:20:54,327 --> 00:20:56,127
Really?

377
00:20:56,127 --> 00:20:59,627
Yes, they say that they found it from under the cellar.

378
00:20:59,627 --> 00:21:01,827
Treasure!

379
00:21:02,527 --> 00:21:04,327
There is a treasure, I'm sure!

380
00:21:04,327 --> 00:21:05,727
I think so too!

381
00:21:05,727 --> 00:21:07,245
I'm getting excited!

382
00:21:07,245 --> 00:21:09,927
Me too!

383
00:21:09,927 --> 00:21:12,827
Now, let's head to the Hagi Castle!

384
00:21:19,827 --> 00:21:24,327
What does Shigeru have to do with those men?

385
00:21:24,327 --> 00:21:26,727
And who is he exactly?

386
00:21:29,527 --> 00:21:32,027
-Hurry up! -Be quiet!

387
00:21:32,027 --> 00:21:35,273
Hey! What do you think you're doing?

388
00:21:35,273 --> 00:21:37,827
-The keys! -You little brat!

389
00:21:37,827 --> 00:21:40,327
Police! This way! Come quick!

390
00:21:40,327 --> 00:21:42,127
Hurry up! We're moving!

391
00:21:44,027 --> 00:21:45,283
Mitsuhiko!

392
00:21:46,327 --> 00:21:47,827
What's going on?

393
00:21:47,827 --> 00:21:49,027
Thanks!

394
00:21:55,627 --> 00:21:57,027
You're not getting away!

395
00:22:04,227 --> 00:22:06,027
Crack!

396
00:22:06,027 --> 00:22:09,307
No, I didn't think they would go this far.

397
00:22:09,307 --> 00:22:12,727
I didn't pay enough attention.

398
00:22:12,727 --> 00:22:16,927
Is there really a treasure that could buy a country?

399
00:22:16,927 --> 00:22:22,327
And who are those men?

400
00:22:22,327 --> 00:22:23,827
And that voice...

401
00:22:23,827 --> 00:22:26,427
Police! This way! Come quick!

402
00:22:26,427 --> 00:22:28,827
I know that voice, and it is...

403
00:23:51,900 --> 00:23:53,420
Next Conan's Hint:

404
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:55,020
"Cat"

405
00:23:56,000 --> 00:23:58,238
Meow! Treasure discovered in the next episode!

406
00:23:58,238 --> 00:23:59,834
How many servings of broiled eel on rice will I be able to eat?

407
00:23:59,834 --> 00:24:00,980
One-track mind.

